# Clinical RAG Extractor — Cursor AI Project Rules

## What This Is
Python implementation of a 5-stage hallucination mitigation pipeline for clinical
data extraction. Companion repo to the paper "Mitigating LLM Hallucinations for
Clinical Data Extraction: A RAG Framework with Structured Output Enforcement".
Uses ONLY public data (CDISC Pilot, synthetic SDTM, public ontologies).

## 5-Stage Pipeline
1. Ingestion — parse clinical docs, section-aware chunking with metadata
2. Retrieval — hybrid BM25 + dense (PubMedBERT) + cross-encoder reranking
3. Generation — LLM with Pydantic-constrained structured outputs (Instructor)
4. Grounding — NLI-based evidence verification, provenance chain
5. Confidence — entropy + self-consistency + NLI → calibrated abstention

## Stack
Python 3.11+, Pydantic v2, LiteLLM, Instructor, sentence-transformers,
rank-bm25, FAISS, HuggingFace transformers (DeBERTa for NLI)

## Rules
- Type hints everywhere, strict mypy
- Pydantic models for ALL data structures
- Every extraction carries ExtractionProvenance
- Output UNABLE_TO_DETERMINE rather than guess
- Safety-critical fields (AE coding) get stricter thresholds
- One import per line (ruff I rules)
- No pickle for deserialization — JSON only

## Domain Terms
SDTM=Study Data Tabulation Model, MedDRA=Medical Dictionary for Regulatory
Activities, LOINC=Logical Observation Identifiers Names and Codes,
CDISC=Clinical Data Interchange Standards Consortium, AE=Adverse Event,
LB=Laboratory, CM=Concomitant Medication, PT=Preferred Term, SOC=System Organ Class
